the class that complains the most, but ask anyone what class they would least like to have in an xp group and I guarantee the majority will answer either wizard or sometimes SK. <br>
We are the only class that I see serving absolutely no &quot;unique&quot; purpose in any given set of circumstances.  For instance enchanters become especially useful during overpulls.  Melee'ers are good in general and necessary in most situations (Pally's get LoH, warriors superior melee and armor wearing skills, Rogues superior dmg output sacrificed for weaker weapons and armor, SK's get HT and lifetap and weak pet etc etc) we have NO unique ability as a class. HELL the only &quot;unique&quot; ability we really had was &quot;less&quot; resists with lure then they @#$#@$ NERFED IT (like the dmg to mana ratio was SO good to begin with) now we get these unique &quot;bane&quot; spells and they @#$@#$ cost expensive reagents (22pp a cast)?  NO other class has this kind of cost, maybe warriors should get fined a reagent each time their cobalt is used or weapon procs (yeah this is another thread altogether check mine on melee's are casters). <br>
<br>
I refuse to be ignored, I worked hard for my wizard, I've endured such @#$#@ to get him where he is, and I refuse to have him dumped on like this.  No I am not retiring my wizard because deep down I have a soft spot for him, and I love playing him even in a limited fashion.  My ultimatum (like I can actually make one) is that they either a) fix wizards or b) tell us something even PRELIMINARY, at least show us they're #$@#$ thinking over there or are listening to us in some manner.  I'm not asking them to promise lower resists, but at least that they're taking in ideas officially and either giving reasons why they're being rejected or some other reason.  I remember reading a long post of wizard complaints they compiled once but were just being considered.  Apparently 2 lvl 60 spells are their cure all.  I don't know what the fix should be, but closing our message boards and putting in 2 high cost lvl 60 spells and a gate hardly seems like a major readjustment at all.    My rant is done, please post your replies (=<br>
